### Frontend (Angular)

#### [NEW] [auth.guard.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/core/guards/auth.guard.ts)
- Create a route guard implementing `CanActivate`.
- Check if the user is authenticated. If not, redirect to `/login` (or role-specific portal login).
- Check if the user has the required role (if role-restricted).

#### [MODIFY] [app-routing.module.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/app-routing.module.ts)
- Secure the main routes layout and sub-routes by registering `canActivate: [AuthGuard]`.

#### [MODIFY] [auth.interceptor.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/core/interceptors/auth.interceptor.ts)
- Intercept outbound requests and append the JWT token in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` (already partially implemented).
- Intercept inbound responses. If a `401 Unauthorized` response is returned, automatically invoke `authService.logout()`, clear the localStorage state, and navigate the user to the login screen. This prevents displaying welcome screens like "Welcome Back, Shivam!" when database is dropped!

